 them—collapse in the face of development reforms. This collaborative volume, involving both Asian and U.S. scholars, explores the impact of changes in women’s rights to housing and land in three socialist countries that are moving toward market economies. The authors focus on such issues as property use and ownership, efforts to recognize women’s economic rights through development programming, poverty and women-headed households, and household bargaining. The final chapter surveys the impact of various development policies, highlighting successes and failures.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / World / Asian.2bisacsh1 aAslanbeigui, Nahid, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHopkins, Barbara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIreson, W. Randall, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIreson-Doolittle, Carol, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJuanhong, Fei, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNgoc Du, Thai Thi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPyle, Jean Larson, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSowerwine, Jennifer, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSummerfield, Gale, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSummerfield, Gale, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aThi Lich, Hoang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTinker, Irene, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTinker, Irene, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aVan Anh, Tran Thi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aV